Essar Oil’s Fourth-Quarter Profit Rises on Refining Margins

-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 
2011-04-11T09:59:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/essar-oil-s-fourth-quarter-profit-rises-on-refining-margins.html
Essar Oil Ltd. (ESOIL) , the operator of
 India ’s second-largest non-state crude oil refinery, posted a 78
percent increase in fourth-quarter profit after margins from
processing gained.  Net income in the three months ended March 31 rose to 3.2
billion rupees ($72 million) from 1.8 billion rupees a year
earlier, the company said in an e-mailed statement today. Gross
revenue increased 24 percent to 148.5 billion rupees.  Refining margins in the quarter were $8.15 a barrel
compared with $5.37 a year earlier. Expansion of capacity at the
Vadinar refinery to 20 million metric tons a year is scheduled
to be completed by September 2012, Essar Oil said.  Essar Oil declined 3 percent to 135.70 rupees at 3:06 p.m.
in Mumbai trading. The stock has dropped 10 percent in the past
year compared with a 7.5 percent increase in the benchmark
Sensitive Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rakteem Katakey in  New Delhi  at 
